                   "message":  "ASSET-STORE-WINDOWS-RENAME: AlreadyExists fallback for LocalCache staging renames\n\nLands a previously-uncommitted, test-backed local change (human-authorized\nsalvage, dispatch 1 of 2).\n\nLocalCache writes atomically via a staging file + fs::rename(staging, dest).\nPOSIX rename(2) atomically REPLACES an existing destination; Windows\nstd::fs::rename instead returns ErrorKind::AlreadyExists when dest exists (it\nmaps to MoveFileEx WITHOUT MOVEFILE_REPLACE_EXISTING). So on Windows every\nrepeated flush_index() fails and leaks .index.staging, and a content-addressed\npayload write whose canonical destination already exists fails and leaks its\nstaging sibling.\n\ncrates/asset-store/src/local.rs:\n- finish_payload_write(): on AlreadyExists + dest exists, the content-addressed\n  path names the same asset id, so discard the staging file instead of leaking\n  it; other errors propagate. Replaces the inline payload-write rename.\n- replace_index_with_staging(): on AlreadyExists + dest exists, remove the\n  existing (recoverable) index then re-rename; other errors propagate. Replaces\n  the inline index-save rename.\n- remove_file_if_exists() helper (NotFound treated as Ok).\n- add ErrorKind to the std::io import.\n- test repeated_flush_replaces_existing_index_without_staging_leak: two\n  put+flush cycles assert the index contains both ids and .index.staging does\n  not leak.\n\nUnix behaviour is unchanged (rename replaces, so the AlreadyExists arms never\nfire). Single file; 0 Cargo.toml.\n\nGate: VERIFY OK 7/7 + 10/10 arch lints (the new test passes on the Windows gate\nhost); cargo check --all-targets clean (no new warnings); nightly fmt clean.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
